{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2024-08-29T18:10:14.353645+00:00", "modified": "2025-02-06T22:44:36.328291+00:00", "id": 13522349, "conceptrecid": "13522348", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.13522349", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.13522348", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.13522349", "metadata": {"title": "A set of principles and practical suggestions for equitable fieldwork in biology.", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.13522349", "publication_date": "2022", "description": "(Uploaded by Plazi for the Bat Literature Project) Field biology is an area of research that involves working directly with living organisms in situ through a practice known as \"fieldwork.\" Conducting fieldwork often requires complex logistical planning within multiregional or multinational teams, followed by collaborative research led by one or a few of the core team members. However, existing power imbalances stemming from geopolitical history, discrimination, and professional position perpetuate inequities in the context of these research endeavors. After reflecting on our own research programs, we propose four general principles to guide equitable, inclusive, ethical, and safe practices in field biology: Be Collaborative, Be Legal, Be Safe, and Be Respectful. Although many field biologists already structure their field programs around these principles or similar values, executing equitable research practices can prove challenging and requires careful consideration, especially by those in positions with relatively greater privilege. Based on experiences and input from a diverse group of global collaborators, we provide suggestions for action-oriented approaches to making field biology more equitable under these guidelines, with particular attention to how those with greater privilege can contribute. While we acknowledge that not all suggestions will be applicable to every institution or program, we hope that they will generate discussions and provide a baseline for training in proactive, equitable fieldwork practices.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Casta\u00f1eda, Valeria Ram\u00edrez", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Westeen, Erin P", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Frederick, Jeffrey", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Amini, Sina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wait, Daniel", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Achmadi, Anang S", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Andayani, Noviar", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Arida, Evy", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Arifin, Umilaela", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bernal, Mois\u00e9s A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sanguila, Marites Bonachita", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Brown, Rafe M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Che, Jing", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Condori, F Peter", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hiller, Anna E", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Iskandar, Djoko T", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jim\u00e9nez, Rosa Alicia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Khelifa, Rassim", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mart\u00ednez-Fonseca, Jos\u00e9 G", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Parra, Juan L", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pe\u00f1alba, Joshua V", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pinto-Garc\u00eda, Lina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ron, Santiago R", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Souza, Sara", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Supriatna, Jatna", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bowie, Rauri C K", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "McGuire, Jimmy A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tarvin, Rebecca D", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/71dc436aa273021a405836cc6593a24c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/96d9575e334ff78d36c2a68bce6550130107768985fc7b808caf5daa31137cd0", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/PL3E9ZE4", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "sc